\label{app:properties}

For every galaxy group we calculate several basic properties. The main properties are the velocity dispersion and the size in the plane of the sky, used for estimating the virial mass and radius of the groups and for the suppression of the FoG redshift distortions. Details about these calculations are given in \citet{2014A&A...566A...1T}. For convenience a condensed description is provided below.

